                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/1214</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Special Representative <persName type="to">Rodgers</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-02T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>116. Newspapers report beginning June 1 all exploiters of petroleum deposits
                    Mexico required pay bimonthly inspection fee three hundred dollars Mexican
                    gold.</p>
                <p>Telegraph whether report correct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
